Revisions to v2 of the WaniKani API are designated by timestamps in the format `YYYYMMDD`.

Breaking changes introduced to the API will be given a new revision timestamp. An example would be the renaming of a field in a resource. Changes which do not change the existing request/response structure will be introduced into all the existing revisions. Examples of non-breaking changes would be the inclusion of a new field in a resource or the addition of new endpoints.

We expect the revision to be included in all API requests to the server in a header that looks like the following: `Wanikani-Revision: <%= current_page.data.api_revision %>`.

See the [list of revisions and changelogs](<%= current_page.data.documentation_root_path %>) for more details.

